Drop the gio-querymodules post-install step: it hard-requires a native
gio-querymodules binary (which e.g. Gentoo ships suffixed as
gio-querymodules-64, so find_program fails) only to refresh the GIO module
cache after installation. We build glib-networking exclusively for the
Android cross target and as a static library — there is no module cache to
refresh, and the tool couldn't produce a target-valid one anyway.

diff --git a/meson.build b/meson.build
--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -146,9 +146,6 @@ subdir('po')
 subdir('proxy')
 subdir('tls')

-# Will automatically pick it up from the cross file if defined
-gnome.post_install(gio_querymodules: gio_module_dir)
